There's no way this thing is 6.7 million IDR, just use Blender (and Blender is not this dogwater) dawg.



0:00 very ugly characters, as in proportions. You can make characters unique, but they made them like Skyrim custom character customization sliders.



0:06 Why the 5 stars?



0:08 There is no absolute lighting control, like there is no believable shadow. like when you port all the assets but use artificial brightness so you can see what you are animating. Not to mention the art direction is not there at all; you cannot put normal everyday items along with abnormal, non-everyday people. It is not immersive and doesn't strike you with "Oh, so this is where the [main character] lives in [universe]."



0:10 Like I said, abnormally looking people in normal-looking places just doesn't add up; it's weird, and viewers' perception will mark it as ugly because they have normal things to compare them with.



0:14 There is absolutely no physics behind that box; they just put a box afloat without tying the box to gravity physics, and the ropes were there to make it look like it was hanging but with no actual connection from one asset to another, and the box itself looks so bad that at first I thought they 3D scanned it, but no, I believe they exported it from open assets because even using a cheap 3D scanner, which is your own phone, will have a greater result. And like I said, there is no lighting entity. Well, there is, but most asset properties aren't tied to said entity, or rather, its shadows don't dynamically react to another object. Thus, some things' shadows don't cast on other things.



0:18 Yeah, no actual lighting to make it believable. I mean, look at those trees.



0:23 Notice how he pointed the megaphone a bit upward? It is because the model arm joint will be unnaturally bent. One way to fix it is by redesigning the megaphone handle to be curve-shaped, but since they took the asset somewhere else, I don't think they can, or they just do not have the will to model it in-house.



0:32 weird hair physics, no cast shadows (background characters have 2 shadows; THERE ARE 2 SUNS IN INDONESIA?!). He is not unique; he is just straight up ugly because there are normal-looking people behind him, and some of these people are weird. Look at the very back; you will see some people that are as tall as an adult knee, wtf.



0:38 weird-looking characters (the right side is the most normal one I've seen lmao), no shadows, no lighting.



0:45: Wtf is this scene?



0:49 insane close-up ugly



0:50 WHERE IS THE LIGHTING? The same walking animation is used by 3 characters; the women are normal looking, but the other people...



0:52 no lighting



0:53 Dude, can we stop for the close-up scenes? There is nothing to be proud of.0:57 generic idle animation

So, what is the plot of the movie? to get the flag. How? I don't fucking know. Seriously, I like the idea of these kids going through all that just for a flag because the flag is that precious to them, but the importance of the flag itself flew over their heads, which made this movie depict that the flag (as in the object) is that valuable, whereasit is not about the flag at all but rather the ideology that the flag upholds. It is just another flag; just buy it off someone else lmao. A different flag won't change anything because both flags are Indonesian flags; it is the message that the flag upholds.
